<dl id="n05015g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05015g">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05015g"> 15(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> says HM himself</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">No dexterity is able to extract more than four or five thousand years from the Scripture since the time of Noah. &ldquo;According to the calculations of Sir Charles Lyell,&rdquo; <mark>says Hugh Miller himself</mark>, &ldquo;no devastating flood could have passed over the forest zone of &AElig;tna during the last twelve thousand years&mdash;for such is the antiquity which he assigns to its older lateral cones, that retain in their integrity their original shape; and the volcanic cones of Auvergne, which enclose in their ashes the remains of extinct animals, and present an outline as perfect as those of &AElig;tna, are older still.&rdquo; <small> G.W. Foote, <a name="BROM" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#BROM"><cite title="source">Bible Romances</cite></a>, 4th ed. (1922) [Noah&apos;s Ark] 63</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
